### User:
in a javascript web app, how do you save text to a local file

### Response:


To save the text in a local file using JavaScript, you would use the `saveAs()` method of the FileSaver object. Here is an example code snippet that demonstrates this functionality:
```javascript
const text = "This is some sample text to be saved.";
// Create a new Blob object from the text
const blob = new Blob([text], { type: 'text/plain' });
// Set the name of the file you want to save it as
const fileName = 'sample-file.txt';
// Use FileSaver to save the file to your computer
saveAs(blob, fileName);
```
